Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 16
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 16

Request for Judicial Notice (RJN)

⚖️ Core Message

Courts can notice certain public records and facts not subject to reasonable dispute.
📖 Lesson Content

1. What qualifies: docket entries, statutes, government records, dates, maps.
2. Attach the source or provide a verifiable link; identify the noticed fact precisely.
3. Don’t smuggle argument; RJN is about authenticity/undisputability.
4. Pair RJN with a short order granting/denying specific items.
📝 Assignment

Draft an RJN of three items: court docket entry, agency webpage, and statute text; attach a short proposed order.
✅ Model Response

REQUEST FOR JUDICIAL NOTICE (excerpt)

1. Dkt 18 (entered Aug. 2, 2025) — existence and date of entry.

2. Agency page [URL] — policy text as of Aug. 1, 2025.

3. Statute [cite] — text reproduced from official source.

 

[PROPOSED] ORDER: Items 1‑3 GRANTED for the fact of existence/text.

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Notice what’s notice‑able — not what’s debatable.
🎨 Visual Concept

A magnifying glass over a statute book and a docket line.
